import React from 'react'; const Resume = () => { const nashtechGlobal = ( <>

Junior Developer At NashTech Global

Secrect Project

Dec-2019 - Present
Project Description
  • 'Secrect Project' is highly regarded as a driving force in financial adviser professional development with their market-leading 'Secrect' product. Annually, 'Secrect' provide Continuing Professional Development (CPD) solutions to corporates and individuals, with over 35,000 users of CPD programs through its online CPD platform, 'Secrect'. The 'Secrect' product has evolved over time and is currently in its 16th year of operation.
  • This project is to develop a new version of 'Secrect' product ('Secrect' V2) to replace the old one. 'Secrect' V2 has 3 main types of user:
    • 'Secrect Project' Admin has ability to manage learning content in form of lesson, quiz or topic and manage Corporates as well as its learners through subscriptions.
    • Corporate Admin has ability to upload their own contents for their users, manage their employees professional development by setting professional development plans, tracking, monitoring and reporting of training completed.
    • Learner has ability to learn and track their learning progress based on the plans that have been set by manager.
Project Technology
  • .NET CORE, Microservices, ReactJS, AWS, Docker, GraphQL, Mulesoft, Moodle, Drupal, Salesforce, OneLogin
My Position
  • Developer
My Responsibility
  • Make the detailed designs for assigned tasks.
  • Write code based on detailed designs and Functional/Requirement Specifications.
  • Perform full unit test on the assigned tasks.
  • Implement unit test.
  • Incident and bug fixing.
  • Review cod.
Team size
  • About 30 people.
); const futurify = ( <>

Junior Developer At Futurify

Project: Beniplus

Sep-2019 - Dec-2019 (90 days)
Project Description
  • Manage Employer, employee and Benefit Health care of employee, check bill physical examination or health-related issues then give money back for employee
Project Technology
  • Java spring boot, ReactJS
My Position
  • Developer
My Responsibility
  • Coder, refactor code and review
  • Wrote code for manage users, roles and permission
  • Wrote code for manage benefit
Team size
  • About 3 people.

Project: MilanoCoffee

May-2019 - Sep-2019 (120 days)
Project Description
  • Manage warehouse order, manage user and franchise agent, booking coffee and food.
Project Technology
  • .NET core 2.0, Angular 7
My Position
  • Developer
My Responsibility
  • Coder, review and refactor code
  • Wrote code for manage users, roles and permission
  • Wrote code get order and products's details
Team size
  • About 8 people.

Project: VietCredit

Feb-2019 - May-2019 (90 days)
Project Description
  • Manage Loan Application, user request Loan profile, use SOAP put to VietCredit Server, run cronjob daily task and get the result then update loan profile in database.
Project Technology
  • .Net core 2.0, SOAP, AngularJS.
My Position
  • Developer
My Responsibility
  • Coder and test, fix bugs.
  • Wrote code for page request loan.
  • Wrote code for import file excell about information of borrower into system, validate and resolve information existed.
Team size
  • About 3 people.

Project: RVezy

Feb-2019 - May-2019 (90 days)
Project Description
  • Manage Loan Application, user request Loan profile, use SOAP put to VietCredit Server, run cronjob daily task and get the result then update loan profile in database.
Project Technology
  • .Net core 2.0, SOAP, AngularJS.
My Position
  • Developer
My Responsibility
  • Coder and test, fix bugs.
Team size
  • About 3 people.
